 National Democratic Front (NDF) has given its verdict on the first 100 days in office of President Muhammadu Buhari’s second term.  The group in its verdict, lauded President Buhari for making a bold and loud statement in governance. NDF made this known through its Secretary General, Dr Bolaji Abdulkadir, at a press conference held on Wednesday in Abuja. The group observed that the president has made a tremendous progress in the health, security, economy, education and agriculture. Continue reading 100 days in office: NDF lauds Buhari for making ‘loud statement’ on governance at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard